We are also working on other communication measures to keep you abreast of strategies, tools and recommendations.

span.font: AASA recognizes your concerns about the encroaching spread of COVID-19 (Coronavirus) and its potential impact on schools, and aims to provide the best, most up-to-date information available from the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC).

font.b: Stay Up to Date and Connected

br.br: With the conversations around COVID-19 growing daily, the AASA communications team created an online platform allowing AASA members and staff to share communication strategies, resources and ideas, engage with colleagues across the nation, and grow personal and professional learning communities.
We also encourage you to visit the Emergency Management, School Safety and Crisis Planning Community to share resources and participate in discussions with fellow administrators.

p.span: The AASA Leadership Network is offering a series of virtual events about topics related to running districts under quarantine, staying connected to staff and students, implementing and ensuring quality distance learning and more.

span.a: Learn About AASA Leadership Network Webinars and Register

div.b: With questions contact AASA Communications Team at webmaster@aasa.org.
